[I] An Amiga emulator written in Rust

[T] Copperline is an Amiga emulator written in Rust, built around a vendored
[T] copy of the pure-Rust m68k CPU core, with a pixels + winit window for video
[T] and stdout for serial.

[U] https://github.com/LinuxJedi/Copperline

[A] Andrew Hutchings
[M] foxdrodd

[C] extra/tool
